body: Thanks @hadusam. I agreed your suggested plan.

To make small changes and easily reviewing, I would like to solve this issue following some steps.
1. Refactor and align the same test cases on each device with current Models.

| Task | Model | x86_64 | ARM | ARM_FPGA |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| classification | lmnet_quantize_cifar10_space_to_depth | o | o | o |
| classification | resnet_quantize_cifar10 | o | o | o |
| object_detection | fyolo_quantize_4_v4 | o | o | o |
| segmentation | lm_segnet_v1_quantize_camvid | o | o | o |

2. Update Models to new ones created by the latest network
I am planning to remove `dlk/example` directory and use external public storage for example models instead of them to keep repository size small.

| Task | Model | x86_64 | ARM | ARM_FPGA |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| classification | LmnetV1Quantize | o | o | o |
| classification | ResNetQuantize | o | o | o |
| object_detection | LMFYoloQuantize | o | o | o |
| segmentation | LmSegnetV1Quantize | o | o | o |

3. Add AArch64 tests

| Task | Model | x86_64 | ARM | ARM_FPGA | AArch64
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| classification | LmnetV1Quantize | o | o | o | o |
| classification | ResNetQuantize | o | o | o | o |
| object_detection | LMFYoloQuantize | o | o | o | o |
| segmentation | LmSegnetV1Quantize | o | o | o | o |
